<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1009] DumpLogSegments tool should return error on non-existing files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1009</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we run the tool on an non-existing file, we get the following&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bin/kafka-run-class.sh kafka.tools.DumpLogSegments --files 00.log&lt;br/&gt;
Dumping 00.log&lt;br/&gt;
Starting offset: 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tool should return an error message instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12663687">KAFKA-1009</key>
            <summary>DumpLogSegments tool should return error on non-existing files</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
